<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-07-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-07-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="41" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d41">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Egan</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-07-11"><hi rend="italic">July 11,
                            1892</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Egan reports that an indemnity for the seamen of the <hi rend="italic">Baltimore</hi> has been agreed to by the minister for foreign affairs,
                        who this day offers $75,000 in gold, and that the Congress will be asked,
                        without delay, for the approval to which the offer is subject. Mr. Egan
                        recommends that it be accepted and confirmed at once.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>